      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can the life list help with burnout?</summary>
        <p>Yes, if managed correctly. By externalizing your goals into a trusted system, you reduce cognitive load. Breaking massive, intimidating goals into small, achievable tickets prevents overwhelm and provides a steady stream of dopamine through incremental wins, which is a powerful antidote to burnout.</p>
      </details>
